---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { MenuExampleBasic, MenuExampleWithSizes, MenuExampleWithCustomTrigger, MenuExampleWithSubmenu } from "../../components/Menu/Example";
---

<Layout>
  <div id="root">
    <div class="flex flex-col h-dvh">
      <div class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">
        <div>
          <div class="mx-auto relative sm:my-10 max-w-4xl">
            <div
              class="bg-surface-dimmed flex items-center flex-wrap justify-center gap-1 pt-2 pb-1 mx-0 sm:mx-10 font-semibold rounded-t border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-t sm:border-x border-surface-outline"
            >
              <a
                class="cursor-pointer transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 text-link-base hover:text-link-hover"
                href="/"><span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">Lobby</span></a
              ><div class="shrink-0">
                <svg
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  width="16"
                  height="16"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  class="tabler-icon tabler-icon-slash"
                  ><path d="M17 5l-10 14"></path></svg
                >
              </div><a
                class="cursor-pointer transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 text-link-base hover:text-link-hover"
                href="/design-system/"
                ><span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">Design System</span></a
              >
            </div><div
              class="relative bg-surface-base px-12 py-10 min-h-dvh sm:min-h-0 sm:border sm:border-surface-outline sm:rounded-lg sm:shadow-xl"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-content-accent text-lg md:text-2xl font-extrabold"
                  >
                    Menus
                  </div>
                </div><div></div>
              </div><div class="mt-2 mb-10">
                Menus are used to display a list of options or actions that a user can choose from. 
                They are typically triggered by a button or icon, and can contain links, actions, or submenu items.
                Operately's menus are built with Radix UI's DropdownMenu component and are fully accessible, following WAI-ARIA design patterns.
              </div>

              <h3 class="font-bold mt-8 text-lg text-content-accent">Basic Menu</h3>
              <p class="text-content-base text-sm mb-4">
                A basic menu with link and action items. Click the three dots to open.
              </p>
              <div class="p-6 border border-surface-outline rounded-lg mb-8 bg-surface-dimmed flex flex-col items-start gap-6">
                <MenuExampleBasic client:load />
                <div class="mt-2 p-4 bg-surface-base rounded border border-surface-outline w-full">
                  <p class="text-sm text-content-dimmed">
                    The basic menu uses the default trigger (three dots) and includes link items and action items.
                    Items can include icons and can be styled as dangerous actions with red text on hover.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h3 class="font-bold mt-12 text-lg text-content-accent">Menu Sizes</h3>
              <p class="text-content-base text-sm mb-4">
                Menus come in different sizes to accommodate various content needs.
              </p>
              <div class="p-6 border border-surface-outline rounded-lg mb-8 bg-surface-dimmed">
                <MenuExampleWithSizes client:load />
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-surface-base rounded border border-surface-outline">
                  <p class="text-sm text-content-dimmed">
                    Available sizes: small (150px), medium (200px), large (225px), xlarge (250px), xxlarge (275px), and xxxlarge (300px).
                    The default size is medium.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h3 class="font-bold mt-12 text-lg text-content-accent">Custom Trigger</h3>
              <p class="text-content-base text-sm mb-4">
                Menus can be triggered by custom elements instead of the default dots icon.
              </p>
              <div class="p-6 border border-surface-outline rounded-lg mb-8 bg-surface-dimmed flex flex-col items-start gap-6">
                <MenuExampleWithCustomTrigger client:load />
                <div class="mt-2 p-4 bg-surface-base rounded border border-surface-outline w-full">
                  <p class="text-sm text-content-dimmed">
                    Custom triggers can be any React element, including buttons, icons, or text.
                    This is useful when you want the menu to be triggered by a specific UI element.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h3 class="font-bold mt-12 text-lg text-content-accent">Submenus</h3>
              <p class="text-content-base text-sm mb-4">
                Menus can contain submenus for hierarchical navigation.
              </p>
              <div class="p-6 border border-surface-outline rounded-lg mb-8 bg-surface-dimmed flex flex-col items-start gap-6">
                <MenuExampleWithSubmenu client:load />
                <div class="mt-2 p-4 bg-surface-base rounded border border-surface-outline w-full">
                  <p class="text-sm text-content-dimmed">
                    Submenus allow for organizing related options into hierarchical structures.
                    When hovering over a submenu item, a new menu will appear to the right with additional options.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h3 class="font-bold mt-12 text-lg text-content-accent">Usage Guidelines</h3>
              <p class="text-content-base text-sm mb-4">
                Follow these guidelines when using menus in your application.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-3 mt-2 mb-8">
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Use menus for secondary actions that don't need to be immediately visible</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Keep menu items short and descriptive</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Group related items together</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Use icons to provide visual cues about the action</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Highlight destructive actions with the danger prop</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2">
                  <div class="font-bold text-content-accent">•</div>
                  <div class="text-content-base">Use submenus sparingly and only for clearly related items</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Animation for menu slide down */
  .animateMenuSlideDown {
    animation: menuSlideDown 0.15s ease-out;
    transform-origin: top center;
  }
  
  @keyframes menuSlideDown {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: scale(0.95) translateY(-5px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: scale(1) translateY(0);
    }
  }
</style>
